      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "CAN BE A RUEBE NZ (10) has been very good against the top mares of late, placing in the Sibelia before drawing widest in the Queen Elizabeth II Mile and going back to the tail before making a move out wide and working home for fifth. Had gone into those races off a string of wins and placings at this circuit and distance. She looks nicely placed. SKY BLU (7) has been close up from wider barriers than this in both outings since scoring a win at this circuit and distance. Can make an impact. MISSAUDACIOUS (8) could be close to a win following back-to-back placings at this circuit and distance, coming from this barrier to go under narrowly last start. NAMAKA (11) draws deepest but is going well with a string of placings from wider or second line draws. FARFALLA STRIDE (6) owns a decent record at this circuit and distance. Has been competitive of late and can feature again.",
